nt: Parkinson's Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people with Parkinson's disease receive personal independence payment at the (a) daily living standard, (b) daily living enhanced, (c) mobility standard and (d) mobility enhanced rate.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","50850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622725","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-01","<p>I refer the hon Member to the statement made by my Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State to the House on this matter on 31 October 2016, Official Report col 679-80.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-11-01T16:17:56.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622725/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622725/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Nissan: Sunderland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to Nissan's announcement of 27 October 2016 on the production of the next Qashqai and X-Trail models in the UK, what support and assurances the Government has offered to that company.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","50793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622726","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-01","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Work by the Automotive Council has identified £6bn per annum additional opportunities for UK suppliers, where they can compete successfully to win this business. The Government is working closely with the Automotive Council and the wider sector to help secure this.</p><p> </p><p>Government support for small and medium sized enterprises, including suppliers to Nissan, is provided through the range of measures and competitive funding competitions. This includes the Advanced Manufacturing Supply Chain Initiative, with projects running through to 2019, and the Advanced Propulsion Centre, which promotes collaborative R&amp;D between suppliers and vehicle makers to develop products to improve vehicle efficiency and reduce emissions.</p><p> </p><p>As part of a wider programme of long term investment in the North East, the Sunderland and South Tyneside City Deal includes a £5million government investment in a new Advanced Manufacturing Park, which will support the local automotive supply chain.</p><p> </p><p>Further support is provided by the North East Automotive Alliance, which runs a supplier competitiveness programme funded by the European Regional Development Fund.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-11-01T16:15:41.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622726/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622726/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Nissan: Sunderland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question LH2367, what steps his Department is taking to ensure small and medium-sized enterprises involved in the supply chain for the production of Nissan vehicles in the North East automotive sector remain competitive.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","50794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622727","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-03","<p>The data shows apprenticeships offered to newly recruited staff for the former Department for Business Innovation and Skills (BIS) and the former Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) which merged to form the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) on 14 July 2016.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BIS apprentices recruited in <strong>London</strong></p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BIS apprentices recruited in <strong>Cardiff</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BIS apprentices who subsequently secured a job in the Civil Service</p></td><td><p>Not known</p></td><td><p>Not known</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>Not yet completed apprenticeship</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DECC apprentices recruited in <strong>London</strong></p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DECC apprentices who subsequently secured a job in the Civil Service</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>Not yet completed apprenticeship</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The apprentices recruited to former BIS in 2014 and 2015 were all recruited as part of the fast track apprenticeship scheme, in to permanent Civil Service posts.</p><p>6 of the apprentices recruited to former DECC in 2015 were recruited as part of the fast track apprenticeship scheme, in to permanent Civil Service posts.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-03T10:50:02.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622727/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622727/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many apprenticeships have been created in his Department in each region in each of the last five years; and how many participants in those apprenticeships subsequently secured a job within the Civil Service.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","50801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622728","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-04","<p>The Department expects to publish the update of our evidence on the levelised costs of electricity generation in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-04T12:36:04.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622728/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622728/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622728/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Electricity Generation: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will publish the evidence used to inform the range of the costs set out for alternative large-scale low carbon generation technologies in the 2020s in his Department's Hinkley Point C Value for Money Assessment.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","50624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622729","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-03","<p>Over the last year Government has acted to level the playing field for UK steel producers in light of the complex global challenges faced by the UK steel sector. Last December Government issued guidance to central government departments on how to ensure that they take full account of the value provided by UK steel producers when conducting their procurement activities. This guidance is also being extended to the wider public sector.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-11-03T17:04:12.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622729/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622729/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622729/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent estimate he has made of the level of procurement of British steel by his Department in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","50630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622730","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-04","<p>The National Audit Office report in question refers to preliminary estimates of levelised cost data from this evidence update. These have not been published. However, we expect to publish the update of the evidence on the levelised costs of electricity generation in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-04T12:37:18.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622730/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622730/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622730/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Electricity Generation: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, for what reasons the range of the costs for alternative large-scale low carbon generation technologies in the 2020s as set out in his Department's Hinkley Point C Value for Money Assessment differs from the assessment of the same technologies in the National Audit Office report on Nuclear power in the UK, published in July 2016.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","50621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622731","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-04","<p>We expect to publish the update of our evidence on the levelised costs of electricity generation in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-04T12:36:40.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622731/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622731/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622731/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Hinkley Point C Power Station: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will publish the evidence used to inform the conclusion in the Hinkley Point C Value for Money Assessment that the same capacity of onshore wind and solar would require significant upgrades to the grid and increase the costs of keeping the system in balance.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","50622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622732","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-04","<p>The Department expects to publish the update of the evidence on the levelised costs of electricity generation in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-04T12:35:22.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622732/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622732/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622732/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-27","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will publish the departmental report on which figures for the levelised cost of generating 1MWh with different technologies in 2025 in the National Audit Office report, Nuclear power in the UK, published in July 2016, are based.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","50623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622733","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-04","<p>The information is not centrally held in the form requested. Over the last year Government has acted to level the playing field for UK steel producers in light of the complex global challenges faced by the UK steel sector. Last December Government issued guidance to central government departments on how to ensure that they take full account of the value provided by UK steel producers when conducting their procurement activities. This guidance is also being extended to the wider public sector.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2016-11-04T11:13:34.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622733/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622733/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622733/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-27","Department for International Trade: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what recent estimate he has made of the level of procurement of British steel by his Department since it was established.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","50627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622734","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-04","<p>We will take advantage of all the opportunities available to us to ensure that Britain becomes the global leader in free trade once we leave the EU. As the Prime Minister has recently said, countries including Canada, China, India, Mexico, Singapore and South Korea have already told us they would welcome talks on future free trade agreements. And we have already agreed to start scoping discussions on trade agreements with Australia. More recently, my Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade announced the establishment of a UK-New Zealand trade policy dialogue that will cover market access and trade policy issues of mutual interest.</p><p> </p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2016-11-04T13:40:24.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622734/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622734/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622734/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-27","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with which governments of non-EU countries he has discussed future trade agreements since his Department was created.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","50688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622735","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-04","<p>The information is not centrally held in the form requested. Over the last year Government has acted to level the playing field for UK steel producers in light of the complex global challenges faced by the UK steel sector. Last December Government issued guidance to central government departments on how to ensure that they take full account of the value provided by UK steel producers when conducting their procurement activities. This guidance is also being extended to the wider public sector.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-11-04T14:24:56.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622735/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622735/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622735/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-27","Department for Exiting the European Union: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent estimate he has made of the level of procurement of British steel by his Department since its creation.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","50626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622736","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-11-07","<p>I refer the Hon member to the response to PQ 47485.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-11-07T12:16:38.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622736/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622736/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622736/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-27","British Nationals Abroad: Property Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 October 2016 to Question 47485, whether member states will be bound by Article 1 of Protocol 1 of the European Convention on Human Rights, in respect of property rights, where the owner is a UK national, after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","50779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622737","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-02","<p>As a new Department, DExEU is not in a position to report on the use of apprenticeships over the last 5 years. Since our creation we have recruited a number of apprentices into the Department and see them as an important means of hiring into the Department.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-11-02T17:22:09.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622737/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622737/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622737/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-27","Department for Exiting the European Union: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many apprenticeships have been created in his Department in each region in each of the last five years; and how many participants in those apprenticeships subsequently secured a job within the Civil Service.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","50807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622738","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-03","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that she wants to protect the rights of UK citizens living in European member states, in the same way that we want to protect the status of EU nationals already living here.</p><p>At every step of these negotiations we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the people of the United Kingdom.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-11-03T16:02:21.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622738/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622738/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622738/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-10-27","British Nationals Abroad: Property Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 13 October 2016 to Question 47485, if he will ensure the rights of UK owners of property in the EU to occupy that property (a) as a main residence while working, (b) as a main residence during retirement and (c) as an occasional residence, after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","50789"
