"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622259","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Challenger 2 Main Battle Tank remains a key capability for the British Army in the Government's Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 and Joint Force 2025 plans. Work is under way, including in relation to the delivery of Challenger 2 capability, to ensure that the Army has the optimum force structure to introduce new capabilities such as the Strike Brigades and a war-fighting division whilst continuing to meet its current and future commitments. At this time no decisions have been reached.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-02T16:41:35.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622259/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622259/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622259/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-26","Challenger Tanks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to reduce the number of regular armoured regiments that operate the Challenger 2 main battle tank; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","50547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622260","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Challenger 2 Main Battle Tank remains a key capability for the British Army in the Government's Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 and Joint Force 2025 plans. As such the Ministry of Defence is investing £53 million in the assessment phase of a Life Extension Programme with further funding allocated for a demonstration and manufacture phase.</p><p>The Challenger 2 Life Extension Programme (C2LEP) is within the assessment phase and until the main investment point is reached, no decision will be made on the number of Challenger 2 tanks that will go through the C2LEP.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-02T16:42:17.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622260/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622260/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622260/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-26","Challenger Tanks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Challenger 2 main battle tanks are expected to go through the Challenger 2 Life Extension Programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","50548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622261","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-03","<p>The P-8A Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft is a mature capability that has been in production for a number of years. There is already an established supply chain, which includes a number of UK suppliers who continue to benefit from this programme.</p><p> </p><p>The aircraft, however, is only one element of the whole programme. As options for future training and support of the aircraft in the UK are refined, there will be a number of opportunities, managed through normal procurement routes, for UK businesses to be involved in this on-going work. An early example is the announcement made at the Farnborough International Air show in July that Boeing would invest around £100 million in an operational support and training facility at RAF Lossiemouth.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-03T16:58:50.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622261/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622261/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/622261/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-26","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to maximise the UK workshare in the P-8 Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","50538"
